<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<title>Assignment 3</title>
<link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
</head>


<body>
<h1>HTML Guide</h1>
<h2>Common HTML Tags outside &lt;body&gt;</h2>
<p>Click <a href="index.html">here</a> to see other page.</p>

<table style="width:100%;">
	<tr>
	<th style="width:50%;">Tag</th>
	<th style="width:30%;">Definition</th>
	<th style="width:20%;">Examples</th>
	</tr>

<tr>
	<td>&lt;DOCTYPE html&gt;</td>
	<td>Defines the document type</td>
	<td></td>
	</tr>
	
	<tr>
	<td>&lt;html lang="en"&gt;</td>
	<td>The lang attribute specifies the language of the element's content.</td>
	<td><img alt="language" style="width:40%;" src="language.jpg"></td>
	</tr>
	
	<tr>
	<td>&lt;charset&gt;</td>
	<td>Defines a thematic change in the content</td>
	<td><img alt="charset" style="width:90%;" src="charset.png"></td>
	</tr>
	
	<tr>
	<td>&lt;title&gt;</td>
	<td>Defines a title for the document </td>
	<td><img alt="title" style="width:80%;" src="title.png"></td>
	</tr>
	
	<tr>
	<td>&lt;internal CSS&gt;</td>
	<td>used to define a style for a single HTML page</td>
	<td><img alt="internal" style="width:80%;" src="internal.png"></td>
	</tr>
	
	<tr>
	<td>&lt;external CSS&gt;</td>
	<td> a separate CSS file that can be accessed by creating a link within the head section of the webpage.</td>
	<td><img alt="external" style="width:80%;" src="external.jpg"></td>
	</tr>
	
	<tr>
	<td>&lt;favicon&gt;</td>
	<td> a small icon associated with a particular website or page that is displayed in an Internet browser</td>
	<td><img alt="favicon" style="width:80%;" src="favicon.jpg"></td>
	</tr>
	</table>
	</body>
</html>